<article id=3D"content" role=3D"main">

<!-- #BeginEditable "Body" -->=20


<h1 class=3D"center">Eigenvector and Eigenvalue</h1>=20


<p>They have many uses!</p>=20
<p>A simple example is that an eigenvector <b>does not change direction</b>=
 in a transformation:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/algebra/images/e=
igen-transform.svg" alt=3D"Eigenvector in transformation" height=3D"244" wi=
dth=3D"548"></p>=20
<p>How do we find that vector?</p>=20


<h2>The Mathematics Of It</h2>=20

<p>For a square matrix <b>A</b>, an Eigenvector and Eigenvalue make  this e=
quation true:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/algebra/images/e=
igenvalue.svg" alt=3D"A times x =3D lambda times x" height=3D"109" width=3D=
"275"></p>=20
<p>Let us see it in action:</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<div class=3D"h3">Example: For this matrix<br>

	<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
	<div class=3D"mat">=20
	<div class=3D"cols2">=20
	<div>=E2=88=926</div>
<div>3</div>
<div>4</div>
<div>5</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [-6,3~4,5] --><br>
an eigenvector is<br>

<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>1</div>
<div>4</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [1~4] --><br>
with a matching eigenvalue of <span class=3D"larger">6</span>
</div>=20

<p>Let's do some <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/algebra/matrix-multi=
plying.html">matrix multiplies</a> to see if that is true.</p>=20
<p><span class=3D"center large">Av</span> gives us:</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols2" style=3D"color:#850;">=20
<div>=E2=88=926</div>
<div>3</div>
<div>4</div>
<div>5</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1" style=3D"color:#f80;">=20
<div>1</div>
<div>4</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt">=3D</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>=E2=88=926=C3=971+3=C3=974</div>
<div>4=C3=971+5=C3=974</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt">=3D</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>6</div>
<div>24</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [-6,3~4,5][1~4] =3D [-6*1+3*4~4*1+5*4] =3D [6~24] -->=20
<p><span class=3D"center large">=CE=BBv</span> gives us :</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"txt" style=3D"width:35px">&nbsp;</div>
<div class=3D"txt" style=3D"color:#05c;">6</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1" style=3D"color:#f80;">=20
<div>1</div>
<div>4</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt" style=3D"width:205px">=3D</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>6</div>
<div>24</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- 6[1~4] =3D [6~24] -->=20
<p>Yes they are equal!</p>=20
<p>So we get <span class=3D"large">Av =3D =CE=BBv</span> as promised.</p>=
=20
</div>=20

<p>Notice how we multiply a <b>matrix</b> by a <b>vector</b> and get the sa=
me result as when we multiply a <b>scalar</b> (just a number) by that <b>ve=
ctor</b>.</p>=20


<h2>How do we find these <span class=3D"center">eigen things?</span></h2>=
=20

<p>We start by finding the <b>eigenvalue</b>. We know this equation must be=
 true:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">Av =3D =CE=BBv</p>=20
<p>Next we put in an <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/algebra/matrix-t=
ypes.html">identity matrix</a> so we are dealing with matrix-vs-matrix:</p>=
=20
<p class=3D"center large">Av =3D =CE=BBIv</p>=20
<p>Bring all to left hand side:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">Av =E2=88=92 =CE=BBIv =3D 0</p>=20
<p>If <b>v</b> is non-zero then we can (hopefully) solve for <span class=3D=
"center large">=CE=BB</span> using just the <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisf=
un.com/algebra/matrix-determinant.html">determinant</a>:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">| A =E2=88=92 =CE=BBI | =3D 0</p>=20
<p>Let's try that equation on our previous example:</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: Solve for <span class=3D"center large">=CE=BB</span></h3>=20

	<p>Start with <span class=3D"larger">| A =E2=88=92 =CE=BBI | =3D 0</span><=
/p>

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td style=3D"width:10px;">=20
	<div class=3D"larger" style=3D"transform: scaleY(3) translateY(-1px); vert=
ical-align:top;"><b>|</b></div></td>
			<td>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols2">=20
<div>=E2=88=926</div>
<div>3</div>
<div>4</div>
<div>5</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt">=E2=88=92 =CE=BB</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols2">=20
<div>1</div>
<div>0</div>
<div>0</div>
<div>1</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [-6,3~4,5] - &lambda;[1,0~0,1] --></td>
			<td style=3D"width:10px;">=20
<div class=3D"larger" style=3D"transform: scaleY(3) translateY(-1px); verti=
cal-align:top;"><b>|</b></div></td>
			<td><span class=3D"larger"> =3D 0</span></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
<p>Which is:</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"det">=20
<div class=3D"cols2">=20
<div>=E2=88=926=E2=88=92=CE=BB</div>
<div>3</div>
<div>4</div>
<div>5=E2=88=92=CE=BB</div>
</div>=20

</div> <span class=3D"larger">=3D 0</span>=20

</div>=20

<p><!-- [-6-&lambda;,3~4,5-&lambda;] =3D 0 --> Calculating that determinant=
 gets:
</p>=20
<p class=3D"center larger">(=E2=88=926=E2=88=92=CE=BB)(5=E2=88=92=CE=BB) =
=E2=88=92 3=C3=974 =3D 0</p>=20
<p>Which simplifies to this <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/algebra/q=
uadratic-equation.html">Quadratic Equation</a>:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center larger">=CE=BB<sup>2</sup> + =CE=BB =E2=88=92 42 =3D 0</=
p>=20
<p>And <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/quadratic-equation-solver.html=
">solving it</a> gets:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center larger">=CE=BB =3D =E2=88=927 or 6</p>=20
<p>And yes, there are <b>two</b> possible eigenvalues.</p>=20
</div>=20

<p>Now we know <b>eigenvalues</b>, let us find their matching <b>eigenvecto=
rs</b>.</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example (continued): Find the Eigenvector for the Eigenvalue <b>=CE=BB=
 =3D 6</b>:</h3>=20

	<p>Start with:</p>=20
	<p class=3D"center large">Av =3D =CE=BBv</p> Put in the values we know:<br=
>

	<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
	<div class=3D"mat">=20
	<div class=3D"cols2">=20
	<div>=E2=88=926</div>
<div>3</div>
<div>4</div>
<div>5</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>x</div>
<div>y</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt">=3D 6</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>x</div>
<div>y</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [-6,3~4,5][x~y] =3D 6[x~y] -->=20
<p>After multiplying we get these two equations:</p>

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td style=3D"text-align:right;">=E2=88=926x + 3y</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; width:25px;">=3D</td>
			<td>6x</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"text-align:right;">4x + 5y</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; width:25px;">=3D</td>
			<td>6y</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
<p>Bringing all to left hand side:</p>

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td style=3D"text-align:right;">=E2=88=9212x + 3y</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; width:25px;">=3D</td>
			<td>0</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"text-align:right;">4x =E2=88=92 1y</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; width:25px;">=3D</td>
			<td>0</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
<p><i>Either</i> equation reveals that <b>y =3D 4x</b>, so the <b>eigenvect=
or</b> is any non-zero multiple of this:</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>1</div>
<div>4</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [1~4] -->=20
<p>And we get the solution shown at the top of the page:</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols2" style=3D"color:#850;">=20
<div>=E2=88=926</div>
<div>3</div>
<div>4</div>
<div>5</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1" style=3D"color:#f80;">=20
<div>1</div>
<div>4</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt">=3D</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>=E2=88=926=C3=971+3=C3=974</div>
<div>4=C3=971+5=C3=974</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt">=3D</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>6</div>
<div>24</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [-6,3~4,5][1~4] =3D [-6*1+3*4~4*1+5*4] =3D [6~24] -->=20
<p class=3D"center">... and also ...</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
