<div>1</div>
<div>0</div>
<div>0</div>
<div>1</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt">=3D</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols2">=20
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></span>=E2=
=88=92=CE=BB</div>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=921</em><strong>2</strong></span></di=
v>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>2</strong></span></div>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></span>=E2=
=88=92=CE=BB</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt"></div>
</div>=20

<!-- [sqr3/2,-1/2~1/2,sqr3/2] - &lambda;[1,0~0,1] =3D [sqr3/2 - &lambda;,-1=
/2~1/2,sqr3/2 - &lambda;]  -->=20
<p>Now the determinant should equal zero:</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"det">=20
<div class=3D"cols2">=20
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></span>=E2=
=88=92=CE=BB</div>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=921</em><strong>2</strong></span></di=
v>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>2</strong></span></div>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></span>=E2=
=88=92=CE=BB</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt">=3D 0</div>
</div>=20

<!-- [sqr3/2 - &lambda;,-1/2~1/2,sqr3/2 - &lambda;] =3D 0 -->=20
<p>Which is:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">(<span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong=
>2</strong></span>=E2=88=92=CE=BB)(<span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em=
><strong>2</strong></span>=E2=88=92=CE=BB) =E2=88=92 (<span class=3D"intbl"=
><em>=E2=88=921</em><strong>2</strong></span>)(<span class=3D"intbl"><em>1<=
/em><strong>2</strong></span>) =3D 0</p>=20
<!-- ( sqr3/2 - &lambda; )( sqr3/2 - &lambda; ) - ( -1/2 )( 1/2 ) =3D 0 -->=
=20
<p>Which becomes this Quadratic Equation:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">=CE=BB<sup>2</sup> =E2=88=92 (=E2=88=9A3)=CE=BB +=
 1 =3D 0</p>=20
<!-- &lambda;^2 - (sqr3)&lambda; + 1 =3D 0 -->=20
<p>Whose roots are:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">=CE=BB =3D <span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</=
em><strong>2</strong></span> =C2=B1 <span class=3D"intbl"><em><i><b>i</b></=
i></em><strong>2</strong></span></p>=20
<!-- &lambda; =3D sqr3/2 +- i/2 -->=20
<p>The eigenvalues are complex!</p>=20
<p>I don't know how to  show you that on a graph, but we still get a soluti=
on.</p>=20

<h3>Eigenvector</h3>=20

<p>So, what is an eigenvector that matches, say, the <span class=3D"intbl">=
<em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></span> + <span class=3D"intbl"><em><i=
><b>i</b></i></em><strong>2</strong></span> root?</p>=20
<p>Start with:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">Av =3D =CE=BBv</p> Put in the values we know:<br>

<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols2">=20
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></span></di=
v>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=921</em><strong>2</strong></span></di=
v>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>2</strong></span></div>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></span></di=
v>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>x</div>
<div>y</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

<div class=3D"txt">=3D (<span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2<=
/strong></span> + <span class=3D"intbl"><em><i><b>i</b></i></em><strong>2</=
strong></span>)</div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>x</div>
<div>y</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [sqr3/2,-1/2~1/2,sqr3/2][x~y] =3D ( sqr3/2 + i/2 ) [x~y] -->=20
<p>After multiplying we get these two equations:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large"><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>=
2</strong></span>x =E2=88=92 <span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>2</str=
ong></span>y =3D <span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong=
></span>x + <span class=3D"intbl"><em><b><i>i</i></b></em><strong>2</strong=
></span>x</p>=20
<!-- sqr3/2 x - 1/2 y =3D sqr3/2 x + i/2 x -->=20
<p class=3D"center large"><span class=3D"intbl"><em>1</em><strong>2</strong=
></span>x + <span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></sp=
an>y =3D <span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></span>=
y + <span class=3D"intbl"><em><b><i>i</i></b></em><strong>2</strong></span>=
y</p>=20
<!-- 1/2 x + sqr3/2 y =3D sqr3/2 y + i/2 y -->=20
<p>Which simplify to:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">=E2=88=92y  =3D  <b><i>i</i></b>x</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">x  =3D  <b><i>i</i></b>y</p>=20
<p>And the solution is any non-zero multiple of:</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div><b><i>i</i></b></div>
<div>1</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [i~1] -->=20
<p>or</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols1">=20
<div>=E2=88=92<b><i>i</i></b></div>
<div>1</div>
</div>=20

</div>=20

</div>=20

<!-- [-i~1] -->=20
<p><b>Wow, such a simple answer!</b></p>=20
<p><i>Is this just because we chose 30=C2=B0? Or does it work for any rotat=
ion matrix? I will let you work that out! Try another angle, or better stil=
l use "cos(=CE=B8)" and "sin(=CE=B8)".</i></p>=20
<p>&nbsp;</p>=20
<p>Oh, and let us <b>check</b> at least one of those solutions:</p>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: center;">=20
<div class=3D"txt"></div>
<div class=3D"mat">=20
<div class=3D"cols2">=20
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=9A3</em><strong>2</strong></span></di=
v>
<div><span class=3D"intbl"><em>=E2=88=921</em><strong>2</strong></span></di=
